    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what the plan covers, based on thorough exploration of the codebase:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n**4 files to change, 1 new file to create:**\n\n### 1. `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`\n- Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` enum (after `Size`)\n- Add `StatsArgs` struct identical in shape to `SizeArgs` (single `pub human: bool` field with the same `--human/-H/--human-readable` flags)\n\n### 2. `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` *(new)*\n- Iterate `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 buckets: Wheels, SourceDistributions, FlatIndex, Git, Interpreter, Simple, Archive, Builds, Environments, Binaries)\n- Per bucket: call `cache.bucket(bucket)` → `PathBuf`, check `.exists()`, then `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` → `u64`  \n- Print `{bucket}: {size}` per line (using `CacheBucket`'s `Display` impl for versioned names like `wheels-v6`)\n- Print `total: {size}` at the end\n- Size formatting: raw bytes or `human_readable_bytes()` → `{:.1}{}` pattern\n- **No preview gate** (unlike `cache_size`)\n\n### 3. `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`\n- Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;`\n\n### 4. `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- Add `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` dispatch arm calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` (3 args, no `preview`)",
